headline: Waukesha-Pearce Industries Named New Trimble Technology Outlet Serving Texas, Louisiana
summary: Trimble® (Nasdaq: TRMB) today announced that Waukesha-Pearce Industries, LLC. (WPI) is the newest construction equipment dealer to become a Trimble Technology Outlet. WPI will now sell Trimble aftermarket grade control technology to customers using Komatsu and Yanmar earthmoving equipment, including dozers, excavators, mini-excavators, motor graders and compact track loaders. headline: 3 Reasons TRMB is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Trimble has been treading water for the past six months, recording a small loss of 1.9% while holding steady at $60.57. However, the stock is beating the S&P 500’s 7.8% decline during that period.
